initial statement:
 984
Your Honor, 

I, David Lambert, appear before this court today to plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified. At the age of 55, with no prior criminal record, I find myself in a position that I never thought I would be in. 

I am deeply remorseful for my actions and understand the gravity of the offense I have committed. I failed to adhere to the court's previous order that disqualified me from driving, and for that, I am truly sorry. It was a momentary lapse in judgment, and for that, I am deeply embarrassed. 

I acknowledge that my disregard for the court's order was the result of my own thoughtlessness. I did not consider the consequences of my actions nor did I fully comprehend the severity of the offense. It is clear to me now that this was a grave mistake, and I take full responsibility for my actions.

I understand that pleading guilty is, in itself, a mitigating factor. To further demonstrate my remorse and commitment to improving myself, I am willing to undertake any necessary courses or programs that would help me better understand the consequences of my actions and prevent me from repeating the same offense in the future. 

I have already suffered greatly as a result of my actions. The shame and regret I feel each day serve as a constant reminder of the magnitude of my mistake. I assure the court that I will do everything in my power to make amends and work towards becoming a law-abiding citizen once again.

In conclusion, I humbly request the court's leniency and understanding. I acknowledge the seriousness of my offense but hope that my clean record, my genuine remorse, and my willingness to make amends will be taken into account during the sentencing process. I am committed to learning from this experience and becoming a more responsible member of society.
